    <summary>Generate informative test pattern wallpapers for every display from a TOML config file or CLI flags.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
## BgRaster

A fast, single-file console application that generates per-output wallpapers
and assigns them directly to every Windows display. Inspired by Sysinternals BgInfo,
built for creative professionals: AV technicians, video engineers, and real-time
graphics specialists.

### Highlights

- **One PNG per display** — each monitor gets a wallpaper sized to its native
  resolution, anchored to its desktop position.
- **Multiple layers** — text, network adapter info, labeled edges, custom logos
  (SVG), alignment grids, crosshairs, and solid backgrounds, each with independent
  positioning and styling.
- **Format strings** — `${tokens}` for dynamic substitution with independent
  line-by-line size and color cycling.
- **Slices** — split any output into multiple regions, each with different settings.
- **Short-lived and idempotent** — runs until done then exits. Skips re-rendering
  when configuration, version, and hardware fingerprint all match the previous run.
- **TOML-first** — full power via `config.toml` with CLI overrides for quick
  experiments. Auto-seeds a config from defaults on first run.
- **Portable** — single-file `.exe` with no runtime dependencies, built for speed
  via NativeAOT compilation.

### Quick start

```powershell
# Install via Chocolatey
choco install BgRaster -y

# Or download from GitHub Releases and run
BgRaster --config .\wallpaper.toml --render-output .\out\ --text-format "Hello World"
```

